<subSubSection id="C37F6528FFA35663FFDD26056DE282EB" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDA36A3FFA35663FFDD26056DE282EB" blockId="1.[112,752,573,981]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FFDD26056D6A836B" bold="true" box="[113,319,573,597]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Revised diagnosis.</emphasis>
The discovery of 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D20FFA35663FE5526066E08836B" authority="Tanasevitch, 2020" authorityName="Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2020" box="[505,605,574,597]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Pseudomicrocentria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uncata" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FE5526066E08836B" box="[505,605,574,597]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">P. uncata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22257CAFFA35663FDC726056EBE836B" box="[619,747,573,597]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, warrants the diagnosis of the genus as given by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF44B52FFA35663FD0E26656CEC83AB" author="Locket" firstAuthor="Locket" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" pagination="361 - 384" refId="ref3510" refString="Locket GH (1982) Some linyphiid spiders from western Malaysia. Bulletin of the British Arachnological Society, 5: 361 - 384." type="journal article" year="1982">Locket (1982)</bibRefCitation>
to be refined. Species of this genus are small-sized (total length 1.10–1.40) with an unmodified carapace. The formula of leg chaetotaxy is 2.2.2.1, metatarsi I–III each with a trichobothrium. The male palp is characterised by a very simple structure of the embolic division, the radix being continuous with the embolus. The palpal structure is very similar to that many erigonine genera, particularly 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D20FFA35663FFDD27656DDE824B" authority="Simon, 1884" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1884" box="[113,395,861,885]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Tapinocyba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FFDD27656CA5824B" box="[113,240,861,885]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Tapinocyba</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF44B52FFA35663FF5727656DDE824B" author="Simon" box="[251,395,861,885]" firstAuthor="Simon" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" pagination="181 - 885" refId="ref3706" refString="Simon E (1884) Les arachnides de France. Volume 5, Part 2. Roret, Paris. Pp. 181 - 885, pl. 27." type="book chapter" year="1884">Simon, 1884</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D20FFA35663FDB927656EBA824B" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1970" box="[533,751,861,885]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Pseudomicrocentria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FDB927656EBA824B" box="[533,751,861,885]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Pseudomicrocentria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D20FFA35663FE0427456E7382AB" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1884" box="[424,550,893,917]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Tapinocyba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FE0427456E7382AB" box="[424,550,893,917]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Tapinocyba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of sulci on the male carapace, as well as by the formula of leg chaetotaxy 2.2.2.1 vs. 1.1.1.1.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37F6528FFA35663FFDD27C56D8B85CB" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDA36A3FFA35663FFDD27C56D8B85CB" blockId="1.[112,752,1021,1269]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FFDD27C56E49852B" bold="true" box="[113,540,1021,1045]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Speciesincludedandtheirdistributions.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C654D20FFA35663FDB327C56CA5850B" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1970" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Pseudomicrocentria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutissima">
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FDB327C56CA5850B" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Pseudomicrocentria minutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F3727633FFA35663FE4020256CA0856B" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">the Democratic Republic of the Congo</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF44B52FFA35663FEAE20056DD2856B" author="Miller" box="[258,391,1085,1109]" firstAuthor="Miller" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" pagination="75 - 166" refId="ref3593" refString="Miller F (1970) Spinnenarten der Unterfamilie Micryphantinae und der Familie Theridiidae aus Angola. Publicacoes Culturais da Companhia de Diamantes de Angola, 82: 75 - 166." type="journal article" year="1970">Miller, 1970</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F3727633FFA35663FE3420056DB3856B" box="[408,486,1085,1109]" name="Nigeria" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
(Locket &amp; Russel-Smith, 1980), and the 
<collectingCountry id="F3727633FFA35663FEB120656E6D854B" box="[285,568,1117,1141]" name="South Africa" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Republic of South Africa</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF44B52FFA35663FDE620656EB4854B" author="Jocque" box="[586,737,1117,1141]" firstAuthor="Jocque" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" pagination="121 - 146" refId="ref3468" refString="Jocque R (1984) Linyphiidae (Araneae) from South Africa. Part I: The collection of the Plant Protection Research Institute, Pretoria. Journal of the Entomological Society of South Africa, 47: 121 - 146." type="journal article" year="1984">Jocqué, 1984</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D20FFA35663FFDD20456E1685AB" authority="Locket, 1982" authorityName="Locket" authorityYear="1982" box="[113,579,1149,1173]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Pseudomicrocentria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FFDD20456DF385AB" box="[113,422,1149,1173]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Pseudomicrocentria simplex</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF44B52FFA35663FE1C20456E1685AB" author="Locket" box="[432,579,1149,1173]" firstAuthor="Locket" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" pagination="361 - 384" refId="ref3510" refString="Locket GH (1982) Some linyphiid spiders from western Malaysia. Bulletin of the British Arachnological Society, 5: 361 - 384." type="journal article" year="1982">Locket, 1982</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is known only from 
<collectingCountry id="F3727633FFA35663FF0720A56D42858B" box="[171,279,1181,1205]" name="Singapore" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Singapore</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF44B52FFA35663FE8820A56DE0858B" author="Locket" box="[292,437,1181,1205]" firstAuthor="Locket" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" pagination="361 - 384" refId="ref3510" refString="Locket GH (1982) Some linyphiid spiders from western Malaysia. Bulletin of the British Arachnological Society, 5: 361 - 384." type="journal article" year="1982">Locket, 1982</bibRefCitation>
). A third species of the genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D20FFA35663FFDC20866C8D85EB" authority="Tanasevitch, 2020" authorityName="Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2020" box="[112,216,1214,1237]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Pseudomicrocentria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uncata" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B911EAB1FFA35663FFDC20866C8D85EB" box="[112,216,1214,1237]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">P. uncata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22257CAFFA35663FF4420856D3F85EB" box="[232,362,1213,1237]" pageId="1" pageNumber="474" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
has been collected on Borneo, East 
<collectingCountry id="F3727633FFA35663FFDF20E56C8085CB" box="[115,213,1245,1269]" name="Malaysia" pageId="1" pageNumber="474">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
and is described below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
